| Feature                        | Description                                                                 |
|--------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Spatial Constraint             | Ensures clusters are spatially contiguous                                   |
| Constraint Matrix              | Encodes adjacency; used to modify similarity matrix                         |
| Modified Similarity Matrix     | Combines feature similarity and spatial adjacency (Hadamard product)        |
| Algorithm Types                | Partitional (spectral clustering), Hierarchical (agglomerative, bisection)  |
| Major Algorithms               | SSC, HSSC, spatially constrained hierarchical (complete-link, UPGMA, Ward)  |
| Evaluation Criteria            | Landscape homogeneity, spatial contiguity, region size balance              |
| Typical Applications           | Regional planning, resource management, precision agriculture, ecology       |

