| Bayesian Contiguity-Constrained Clustering | Custom, Research Code | Page & Quintana (2016), others | Research repos, PyMC, PySAL          |

---

## **How to Get Started**
- **For most users,** start with [PySAL's spopt.region module](https://pysal.org/spopt/api/generated/spopt.region.html) or [ClusterPy](https://github.com/sorate0/ClusterPy), both of which are robust and well-documented.
- **For more advanced/Bayesian approaches,** you may need to look for recent research code or implement your own using libraries like [PyMC](https://www.pymc.io/) for Bayesian models with spatial constraints.

---

**In summary:**  
The most advanced and accessible Python implementations for spatial regionalization are found in [PySAL](https://pysal.org/) and [ClusterPy](https://github.com/sorate0/ClusterPy), supporting algorithms such as SKATER, REDCAP, and more. For hierarchical and Bayesian approaches, you may need to look for research code or extend existing packages.
